Polymorphic Pattern

- good for data which shares many common fields across different documents
- not all fields are present/idenitcal for different documents
- querying can be accomodated through acess to entire collection, i.e. brands, sizes, stock etc.
 

{"category": "Outdoors",
"product_group": "Fishing",
"brand": "Singer",
"article": "Bass-King BL",
"units": [ {
	"type": "Jnr"
	"length": 80}, 
{
	"type": "Pro"
	"length": 140
	} ]
}

{"category": "Garden",
"product_group": "Pool",
"brand": "Blue Diamond",
"article": 	"Family Bay Pool",
"dimensions": [ {
	"type": "assembled",
	"length": 185,
	"width": 220,
	"depth": 40,
	} ,
{
	"type": "packaging",
	"length": 65,
	"width": 90,
	"dpeth": 50
	]
}
